Project structure:
- backend/ — Medusa.js v2 Node.js API server
- storefront/ — Next.js 15 App Router TypeScript storefront

Tech stack:
- Next.js 15 with App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4
- Medusa.js v2 for e-commerce backend
- Supabase for PostgreSQL database and file storage
- Stripe for payments via @medusajs/payment-stripe
- Resend for transactional emails
- @medusajs/js-sdk for storefront API calls
- Framer Motion for animations
- lucide-react for icons

Coding conventions:
- All Next.js components use TypeScript with proper typing
- Server components by default, "use client" only when needed (useState, useEffect, event handlers)
- Tailwind for all styling — no CSS modules, no styled-components
- CSS custom properties for theme colors: --bg, --fg, --muted, --border, --card
- Dark theme: black background (#000000), near-white text (#f0f0f0)
- Prices are stored in cents in Medusa and must be divided by 100 for display
- Cart state is managed via CartContext in src/context/CartContext.tsx
- Medusa SDK client is exported from src/lib/medusa.ts as `sdk`
- Utility functions live in src/lib/utils.ts
- No default export for utilities, named exports only
- All components use named exports (export default function ComponentName)
- Import alias @/ maps to src/
- In Next.js 15, dynamic route params are Promise-based (await params)

Design style:
- Minimal, high-contrast dark aesthetic
- Typography: tight letter-spacing on headings, tracking-widest on labels and buttons
- Buttons: outlined, uppercase, letter-spaced — no rounded corners on CTA buttons (use rounded-sm at most)
- Product images use aspect-[3/4] ratio with object-cover
- Hover states: subtle scale on product images (scale-[1.04]), color transitions on links/buttons
